article.headline: Reynolds scores career-high 39 as Green Bay knocks off Wright State 88-77

images.name: Tanner Holden throws down big slam vs. Green Bay Phoenix
images.caption: Tanner Holden throws down big slam vs. Green Bay Phoenix

article.linkText: Reynolds scores career-high 39 as Green Bay knocks off Wright State 88-77
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- — Noah Reynolds scored a career-high 39 points, tied for the sixth-most in program history, to lead Green Bay past Wright State 88-77 on Friday. Reynolds was 14 of 19 from the field, including 5 of 6 from distance — for the most points by a Division I player in a regulation game this season. Reynolds also had six assists for the Phoenix (7-7, 2-1 Horizon League). Rich Byhre shot 6 for 9, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc to add 17 points. Elijah Jones shot 4 of 4 from the field to finish with nine points. Tanner Holden and Trey Calvin each scored 23 points for the Raiders (6-7, 1-1). Brandon Noel also had 10 points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
